  "text": "The Kafka producer record flow begins when a ProducerRecord is created by the user. The record is then passed to the producer's send() method, which delegates to RecordAccumulator.append() (line 275 in RecordAccumulator.java). This method accumulates records into batches of MemoryRecords, managing partition assignment and buffer allocation.\n\nThe RecordAccumulator maintains a queue of ProducerBatches grouped by topic and partition. When append() is called, it either appends the record to an existing in-progress batch or creates a new batch if needed. The method uses partitioner logic to determine the target partition and manages buffer allocation from a BufferPool.\n\nThe Sender thread's main loop is implemented in Sender.run() and Sender.runOnce() (lines 236 and 305 in Sender.java). In runOnce(), the sender calls sendProducerData() which invokes RecordAccumulator.ready() to identify partitions with batches ready to send. The ready() method checks batch readiness using batchReady() (line 603 in RecordAccumulator.java), which evaluates if a batch is full, if linger time has expired, or if a flush is in progress.\n\nOnce ready batches are identified, Sender calls RecordAccumulator.drain() (line 954 in RecordAccumulator.java) to extract the ready batches grouped by broker node. This drains batches from the accumulator without removing them permanently, as they may need to be retried.\n\nThe drained batches are then processed by Sender.sendProduceRequests() (line 856 in Sender.java), which groups them by destination node and calls sendProduceRequest() for each node (line 864 in Sender.java). This method constructs a ProduceRequest containing the serialized MemoryRecords and creates a ClientRequest object.\n\nThe actual network transmission occurs when Sender calls client.send() (line 914 in Sender.java), which delegates to NetworkClient.send() (line 541 in NetworkClient.java). The NetworkClient converts the request to a Send object and places it in the selector's outgoing queue via selector.send(new NetworkSend()) (line 617 in NetworkClient.java).\n\nWhen the broker responds with a ProduceResponse, Sender.handleProduceResponse() (line 568 in Sender.java) processes the response. This method checks for errors, handles retries, and calls completeBatch() to finalize the batch processing, invoking the user's callback with RecordMetadata containing the assigned offset and timestamp.\n\nThis complete chain ensures reliable, batched delivery of producer records through the Kafka cluster with proper error handling, retries, and acknowledgment management."
}

